reviews.text: Great, it has good facilitys and staff are very helpful☺☺☺☺☺

Great station, staff and amnesties (for a station) :

`Welcome aboard this Southeastern Service to London Charing Cross, calling at St Leonards Warrior Square, Battle, Wadhurst, Tunbridge Wells, High Brooms, Tonbridge, Sevenoaks, Orpington, London Bridge, Waterloo East, and London Charing Cross. This train is formed of 8 coaches. If you see anything suspicious, please report it to a member of staff, or the police.`

`The next station is, St Leonards Warrior Square.`

Nailed it... everyday...

A modern station with access to many locations.
Platform 1 is not usually in use.
Platform 2 is for services to Brighton, Eastbourne and Ashford.
Platform 3 is for Ore, and, rarely, SouthEastern services to London Charing Cross and London Cannon Street, some terminating early at Tonbridge.
Platform 4 is where all SouthEastern services are normally found.
An attractive new modernist station which serves its purpose very well with an integrated bus and coach depot
